Package de.rumford.tradingsystem

Class EWMAC

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.rumford.tradingsystem.Rule
      • de.rumford.tradingsystem.EWMAC
  • public class EWMAC
extends Rule
    The EWMAC is a non-binary Rule utilizing the different horizons of its 2 underlying EWMA. When the shorter horizon EWMA raises above the longer horizon EWMA in value the underlying asset has been rising in the not-so-distant past and is thus expected to rise further, and vice-versa.
    Author:
    Max Rumford

      • EWMAC

        public EWMAC​(BaseValue baseValue,
             EWMAC[] variations,
             LocalDateTime startOfReferenceWindow,
             LocalDateTime endOfReferenceWindow,
             int longHorizon,
             int shortHorizon,
             double baseScale)
        A rule based on the relation between two exponentially weighted moving averages - EWMAs. The EWMAC assumes that an asset is rising in value, if its short term values are greater than its long term values. If the short horizon EWMA is greater than the long horizon one, a positive forecast is given. Else, a negative forecast is produced.

        This non-binary rule allows for a base value scale independent detailed forecast calculation. The greater the difference between the two EWMAs the greater in extent the forecast will be.

        Parameters:
        baseValue - Same as in Rule(BaseValue, Rule[], LocalDateTime, LocalDateTime, double).
        variations - EWMAC[] An array of three or less rules. Represents the variations of this rule. Same limitations as in Rule(BaseValue, Rule[], LocalDateTime, LocalDateTime, double).
        startOfReferenceWindow - Same as in Rule(BaseValue, Rule[], LocalDateTime, LocalDateTime, double).
        endOfReferenceWindow - Same as in Rule(BaseValue, Rule[], LocalDateTime, LocalDateTime, double).
        longHorizon - int The horizon of the long horizon EWMA. Should be 4* shortHorizon, but can be anything greater than shortHorizon.
        shortHorizon - int The horizon of the short horizon EWMA. Must be greater or equal to 2;
        baseScale - Same as in Rule(BaseValue, Rule[], LocalDateTime, LocalDateTime, double).
